org.teatrove.trove.file
Class MultiplexFile

java.lang.Object
  org.teatrove.trove.file.MultiplexFile

public class MultiplexFile
extends Object

MultiplexFile is a growable list of FileBuffers, stored completely within another FileBuffer. MutiplexFile forms the basis for small database systems.

Author:
Brian S O'Neill

MultiplexFile

public MultiplexFile(FileBuffer fb,
                     int reserved,
                     int blockSize,
                     int blockIdScale,
                     int lengthScale)
              throws IOException
Creates a new MultiplexFile, destroying the contents of the given FileBuffer. If the FileBuffer implements TxFileBuffer, MultiplexFile will use its transaction features.

Parameters:
fb - FileBuffer to store data for MultiplexFile
reserved - Number of bytes to reserve before the MultiplexFile header.
blockSize - Size of file blocks, in bytes
blockIdScale - Number of bytes to use for storing block ids
lengthScale - Number of bytes to use for storing file length
Throws:
IOException
